## Winner

**D full** — RAGAS mean and L7 pass rate agree

RAGAS mean: 0.661  |  L7 pass rate: 0.900

## Interpretation Notes

- Config D wins on both criteria. The pattern **prec(C) > prec(B)** and
  **recall(B) > recall(C)** is typical: reranking improves retrieval
  *quality* (precision), hybrid improves retrieval *completeness* (recall).
  Together they improve both.
- The L7 jump from 0.700 (A/B) to 0.800 (C) to 0.900 (D) shows the
  two techniques are complementary, not redundant.
- Smoke set numbers are noisy (10 questions). Confirm on full 30-question
  eval before reporting as a canonical improvement.

